<!--Advanced Inputs-->
<h5 id="advanced-inputs" class="mt-3">Advanced Inputs</h5>
<p class="mb-0">These settings are optional. You can change them to control how FishTales finds reports and summarizes them.</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Model:</strong> Pick which Gemini AI model you want to use. Different models may give slightly different results. See available models at
        <a href="https://ai.google.dev/models/gemini" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ai.google.dev</a>.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>gemini-2.5-flash</code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Token Limit:</strong> The maximum amount of text the model can read and summarize at once. Too high can cause errors, too low might miss details.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>50,000</code> (<em>Max:</em> <code>100,000</code>, <em>Min:</em> <code>10,000</code>)
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Crawl Depth:</strong> How many links the scraper will follow on a page to find more reports. Higher numbers may find more reports but will take longer.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>25</code> (<em>Max:</em> <code>25</code>, <em>Min:</em> <code>5</code>)
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Summary Prompt:</strong> Instructions for the AI on how to summarize each report. You can change it to get summaries in a style you like.<br>
        <em>Optional:</em> Leave as default if unsure.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Merge Prompt:</strong> Instructions for combining multiple summaries into one final report. You can customize the style or format.<br>
        <em>Optional:</em> Leave as default if unsure.
    </li>
</ul>
